      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "@laanwj The case of CreateNewBlock calling ConnectBlock directly is an argument in favor of why ConnectBlock shouldn't do wallet callbacks - it's a more low-level function that just applies the UTXO state changes of a block. As @cozz says, ConnectTip is called indirectly when a new block gets accepted.\n",
